<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/940: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-29T17:00:00+07:00">June 29,
                                    1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 29—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1055. TF–136. From Adler to Secretary [of] Treasury only. Reference my
                            TF–135 of June 26. Dr. Kung informed me yesterday that he had instructed
                            Dr. Soong to approach the Treasury officially and ask for revision of
                            the 1941 Agreement in the spirit of Lend-Lease. [Adler.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>